      • getProcedureTokens

        public java.util.List<Token> getProcedureTokens​(java.util.List<Token> fileList,
                                                java.lang.Integer currentTokenIndex)
        Break down a file of tokens to just those tokens for a method. A method doesn't have to be specified - the braces are kept track of. When the the count of brace pairs is 0 then processing is stopped.
        Parameters:
        fileList - the list of tokens for a file
        currentTokenIndex - the index into the list of tokens for a file
        Returns:
        the list for a method
